        <h1>Data Quality</h1>
        <article class="mod-content-article mod-data-quality">
            <p>At NGO Aid Map, we think of data quality as having four dimensions:
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong>  the degree to which information provided correctly reflects the work being done. We depend on InterAction members to provide accurate information on their work.</li>
                    <li><strong>Completeness:</strong>   the percentage of projects with information for a given data field.</li>
                    <li><strong>Comprehensiveness:</strong>   the share of an organization’s total work published on NGO Aid Map.</li>
                    <li><strong>Timeliness:</strong>   how soon a project's information is shared after its start date.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
		
            <p>To help our visitors better understand the quality of the data on the site, we’ve created visualizations for two of these elements: completeness and timeliness.</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li id="viz1link" tabindex=1 class="li-click">Visualization #1:   Completeness (All Active Projects)</li>
                <li id="viz2link" tabindex=2 class="li-click">Visualization #2:   Completeness by organization</li>
                <li id="viz3link" tabindex=3 class="li-click">Visualization #3:   Most, Average, and Least Timely Organizations</li>
            </ul>

            <div id="viz1_anchor" class="subtitle-top">
                <h3 id="viz_subtitle" class="viz-subtitle"><strong>Completeness</strong> | <span class='subtitle-smaller'>Provision of data per field</span></h3>
                <p>Participants can provide a range of information for each project, with certain data fields required (indicated by an asterisk) and the others optional. Completeness is measured as the percentage of all projects for which data is provided for a given field. Please note that not all fields are applicable for all projects. Data for certain fields may also not be provided due to privacy, security or other concerns.</p>
                <p>For more information about these fields, see the <a href="//www.interaction.org/sites/default/files/ngoaidmap/project-reporting-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Project Reporting Guidance</a> document on the <a href="//www.ngoaidmap.org/p/data-guidance" target="_blank">Data Guidance</a> page.</p>
            </div>
                            
